<paragraph blockId="13.[827,1444,1360,1688]" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis box="[827,1143,1360,1381]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">
Remarks: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kise &amp; Montenegro &amp; Santos &amp; Hoeksema &amp; Ekins &amp; Ise &amp; Higashiji &amp; Fernandez-Silva &amp; Reimer" authorityYear="2022" box="[963,1143,1360,1381]" class="Anthozoa" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Vitrumanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="13" pageNumber="336" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Vitrumanthus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is distinguished from genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kise &amp; Montenegro &amp; Santos &amp; Hoeksema &amp; Ekins &amp; Ise &amp; Higashiji &amp; Fernandez-Silva &amp; Reimer" authorityYear="2022" box="[912,1052,1391,1413]" class="Anthozoa" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Churabana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="13" pageNumber="343" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">Churabana</taxonomicName>
by its marginal musculature. In 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kise &amp; Montenegro &amp; Santos &amp; Hoeksema &amp; Ekins &amp; Ise &amp; Higashiji &amp; Fernandez-Silva &amp; Reimer" authorityYear="2022" box="[864,1034,1421,1442]" class="Anthozoa" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Vitrumanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="13" pageNumber="336" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[864,1034,1421,1442]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">Vitrumanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, cyclically transitional marginal musculature with several mesogleal lacunae was observed, while in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kise &amp; Montenegro &amp; Santos &amp; Hoeksema &amp; Ekins &amp; Ise &amp; Higashiji &amp; Fernandez-Silva &amp; Reimer" authorityYear="2022" box="[1046,1178,1483,1504]" class="Anthozoa" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Churabana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="13" pageNumber="336" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1046,1178,1483,1504]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">Churabana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cteniform endodermal marginal musculature with comb-like mesogleal pleats was seen. Molecular phylogenetic analyses clearly support the distinctiveness between 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kise &amp; Montenegro &amp; Santos &amp; Hoeksema &amp; Ekins &amp; Ise &amp; Higashiji &amp; Fernandez-Silva &amp; Reimer" authorityYear="2022" box="[1258,1390,1575,1596]" class="Anthozoa" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Churabana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="13" pageNumber="336" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1258,1390,1575,1596]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">Churabana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kise &amp; Montenegro &amp; Santos &amp; Hoeksema &amp; Ekins &amp; Ise &amp; Higashiji &amp; Fernandez-Silva &amp; Reimer" authorityYear="2022" box="[827,985,1605,1626]" class="Anthozoa" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Vitrumanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="13" pageNumber="336" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[827,985,1605,1626]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">Vitrumanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In the 16S-rDNA region, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kise &amp; Montenegro &amp; Santos &amp; Hoeksema &amp; Ekins &amp; Ise &amp; Higashiji &amp; Fernandez-Silva &amp; Reimer" authorityYear="2022" box="[1284,1442,1605,1626]" class="Anthozoa" family="Parazoanthidae" genus="Vitrumanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Zoantharia" pageId="13" pageNumber="336" phylum="Cnidaria" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1284,1442,1605,1626]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">Vitrumanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a unique deletion of 15 bp (positions 
<quantity box="[1277,1399,1636,1658]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6322" metricValueMax="3.81" metricValueMin="3.4543999999999997" pageId="13" pageNumber="336" unit="in" value="143.0" valueMax="150.0" valueMin="136.0">136–150 in</quantity>
our alignment).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[827,1442,1748,1892]" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">
<emphasis box="[827,970,1748,1769]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">Etymology:</emphasis>
The generic name is derived from the Latin word 
<emphasis box="[1033,1134,1779,1800]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">vitruma</emphasis>
, glass, and Greek word 
<emphasis box="[827,908,1809,1830]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="336">anthos</emphasis>
, flower, referring to the appearance of this genus. Gender masculine. The Japanese name is 'Ruri-sunaginchaku'.
</paragraph>
